description:
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Public Health 0-19 Administrator - 12 month fixed term secondment &lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;We are looking for a fulltime administrator to join our busy Single Point of Access administration hub (SPOA) based at the Pat Lewis Centre in Hemel Hempstead assisting the Public Health Nursing teams in West Hertfordshire (Health Visiting and School Nursing). The hub is open 8 am to 5 pm, 5 days per week. No weekend working required.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The successful applicant will be required to work from &lt;strong&gt;9am -5pm over 5 days.&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Please be aware that these roles are based in an office and not a health clinic.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The role involves taking calls from our clients, inputting into SystmOne and making appointments. You will be sending letters and questionnaires out to parents. You will need to be confident on the phone and computer literate, with SystmOne experience being desirable and knowledge of NHS. net/ Outlook.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The team work from a set of standard operating guidance templates&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;You will be dealing with electronic referrals that come in from various sources, as tasks or by emails on the NHS. net account.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;You will be joining a well-established team of administrators who would support you and help with any training needs.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;We have a comprehensive induction programme and extensive training package to support the right person.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;In addition to the basic salary, this post attracts a High Cost Area Supplement of 5% of basic salary subject to a minimum payment of £1,017 and a maximum payment of £1,762 per annum (pro rata where applicable).&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;You must hold a full valid driving licence and access to a car to use regularly for business purposes is essential (unless you have a disability as defined by the Equality Act 2010).’&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;For further details / informal visits contact:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Name: Jackie Robbins&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Job title: Public Health Nursing SPOA Team leader&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Email address: Jackie.robbins@nhs.net&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Telephone number: 07768- 600455&lt;/p&gt;
